Head east from Seattle to Gold Bar.  Turn right/south onto Dorman road.  Cross railroad tracks, bear right.  Follow path for .1 mile to Skykomish river side.  Sample site is 30m removed from river embankment.
Entered the Willapa NWRFound first safe pull out with BLM.
Exit 52 off I-5Barnes DrGated spur road into DNR land. State Timber Sale land.

Travelling West on National Forest Development Road 90, approximately 7 miles past the road for Twin Falls Campground. There is a "pullout" on driver's left, opposite a cliff band, and a visible abundance of mature Bigleaf Maples on the south side of the road. We walked for approx. 1 min West on road 90 and located a rocky creek drainage on the south side of the road that descended down to the Lewis River. We descended approx. 200 feet to the riverside, and then walked up river approx. 300 feet. This mature tree was visible from the river, so we walked approx. 200 feet north to reach it. The sample tree is in a south facing opening surrounded by other Bigleaf Maples and Vine Maples.

Drove W along WA forest road 90, turned onto forest road 83 going N, parked at the Mt. St. Helens National Volcanic Monument sign, hiked at 117 degrees into the forest until we found a suitable tree, 300 ft. From the road
I am just east of the Catherine creek trail 021, about a half mile up from the parking lot on old hwy 8 on the WA side of the Columbia river gorge (near coyote wall TH)
Due south about 100m from the panther creek falls parking lot outside of Carson, WA

From Oakridge, OR take U.S. Forest Service route 19 (West Cascades Scenic Byway) north. After passing Roaring River campground take a right onto FS road 1964. Travel for approximately 2 miles and the sampling site will be on the left.

From Oakridge, OR travel South on U.S. Forest Service route 21 for approximately 8 miles to the Bingham boat ramp. Turn left onto USFS road 2118. Travel approximately 1.5 miles and the. Turn right onto USFS service road 479 at Coffeepot Creek travel about 1 mile along the creek to the first bridge over the creek. The sampling site is about 200m upstream of the bridge o on the North bank.

2.8km east of Roman Nose Mtn in Oregon. Traveling West on OR rt. 126 from Veneta take left onto Siuslaw rd which follows the Siuslaw River. After approximately 1.5km turn right onto Whittaker Creek rd.  Continue for approximately 1.25km and bear left onto Dunn Ridge rd. Follow the paved road for roughly 10km until the intersection with Roman Nose rd. (Also paved but with no signage), turn left. Follow this road for another 1.5-2km and there will be a large  turnout with old dirt fill on the right. 200m past this is an abandoned BLM logging road on the right. Walk about 500-600m down this road and the sampling site is on the left just off the trail.

Treehorn campsite, in Umpqua National Forest, OR. We drove 3/4 mile past the campsite entrance, along the forest service road, until we reached a fork in the road where it passed over a stream.  The tree is approximately 50 ft from the right branch of the road.
Drove 7 miles into Black Creek Rd where NF-040 and Black Creek Rd intersect going over a river. Sampling tree about 10 ft from road and 100 ft from river, at the bottom of a hill.
From Gold Beach,OR, we traveled East on Jerry's Flat Rd, turned right onto Forest Service Rd 3313. We drove 2.5 mi on that road till we found a tree.

From Sixes, OR, we drove East on Sixes River Rd for 20 miles, which turns into a Forest service rd. From the service road, we parked near a maple grove and walked 200 m down an old logging road to access our tree.
Took 101 N , got off at 20 W at the town of Willits. Drive 7.5 miles on 20 W, found small trail with a few large bigleaf maples on the right hand side

From Forest of Nisene Marks State Park (Aptos, CA) entrance station parking area on Aptos Creek Rd: Take Split Stuff trail to Aptos Rancho Trail. Take left on Aptos Ranch Trail and head south on Aptos Rancho Trail for approximately 0.2 miles. Tree is on the right side of the trail right before the wreckage of an old car on the left of the trail. If you reach the point where the trail crosses Aptos Creek (a couple hundred feet past sampling site) you’ve gone too far.

From main parking lot in Rancho San Antonio County Park in Cupertino, CA:Take Permanente Creek Trail for 0.3 miles. Follow signs for Lower Meadow Trail to Deer Hollow Farm. From Deer Hollow Farm take the Wildcat Loop Trail for approximately 0.45 miles. Sample site is to the left of the trail on the opposite side of Ohlone Creek approximately 100-200 feet before the junction with Stephen E. Abbors Trail.
Sample obtained at the lower area of Nacimiento Ferguson Road on Los Padres National Forest Land, off Highway 1, south of Big Sur.

Tree is at sea level down a trail in a valley next to the coast, tree is on flat ground.
